## Concern A — Biome backgrounds

Replaced the two `<div>` gradients + 6 CSS triangle trees in `renderHero()` with a single DPR-aware `<canvas>` driven by a 60fps `requestAnimationFrame` loop. Six biome painters, each with a layered parallax background + 3-5 atmospheric props + subtle animation:

| Biome | Sky | Mid silhouette | Foreground | Animation |
|-------|-----|---------------|------------|-----------|
| `forest_summer` | green-deep gradient + mist band | distant pagoda + 7 pine ridge | grass-stipple floor | 4 paper lanterns bob @ 1.4 Hz with warm radial glow |
| `forest_autumn` | amber-rust gradient | wavy ridge + 5 maple silhouettes (3-ellipse crowns) | leaf-litter stipple | 14 falling leaves drift + sway downward |
| `cold_stone` | blue-grey gradient | 8-peak jagged mountains with white snow caps | 5 ice spires + snow stipple | 22 snowflakes drift downward with horizontal sway |
| `temple` | red-brown gradient | 3-tier pagoda silhouette dominating mid-frame | sand-stone stipple | 18 ember motes rise upward with brightness pulse |
| `cave` | black-purple gradient | top ceiling silhouette + 7 stalactites + edge highlights | wet rock + 5 stalagmites | water-drip glints flash on stalactite tips periodically |
| `eldritch` | deep-violet gradient | violet star field + 6 broken sigil shards on horizon | violet-stone floor | 4 sigil glyphs (circle + crosshair) pulse @ 2.5 Hz |

All painters take `(ctx, w, h, t, isNight, pal)`. Night mode darkens each biome's palette without changing structure. Deterministic `_hash(i)` pseudo-noise lets stipple/star fields stay still across frames without storing arrays.

**rAF lifecycle**: module-scope `_menuRaf`, `cancelMenuLoop()` called from:
- `renderHero()` re-entry (carousel arrow / mode pill change)
- `switchTab(tab !== 'hunt')` (leaving Hunt)
- `startHunt()` (entering a stage)
- `document.visibilitychange` (background tab → save CPU)

Verified no leak: after switching to Forge, canvas pixel sample stayed identical for 300ms; after returning to Hunt, character canvas pixel sums drifted across 3 samples (idle bob alive). Zero console errors.

## Concern B — Character preview

Replaced the `radial-gradient` blob `<div>` with a 96×140 `<canvas>` overlaid on the biome canvas at `bottom:18%`, centered. `drawMenuCharacter(ctx, cx, cy, t, color, accent)` mirrors the body of `hunt-render.js` `drawAnimeGirl` (legs / skirt / shirt / sash / arms / head / hair / eyes) at 2× scale, idle facing-S — no rotating scythe (this is the at-rest menu pose).

**Tier-derived tinting**: reads `WG.AscendSkins.currentTier(activeId)` and uses `tier.color` for the skirt + `tier.accent` for sash, shoes, hair ribbon. Gives each unlockable character (lantern_acolyte through cap_apprentice) visible identity in the preview without needing per-character sprite assets. Falls back to `pal.accent` if no tier resolved.

**Idle bob**: `Math.sin(t * 2π / 1.5) * 2` px Y offset (2px @ 1.5s period). Soft ground shadow ellipse `(14×4)*scale` at 45% black for contact weight. Tiny rim-light dot on cheek for liveness.

## Concern C — Polish

**Vignette** (`renderHero`): radial-gradient `<div>` overlay, `mix-blend-mode: multiply`, opacity 0.4 — drops focus toward frame center without crushing biome art. Sits at z-index 2, between biome canvas (z 1) and chrome (z 3).

**Glyphic title divider**: stage name now sits above a three-piece divider (gradient line ↔ glowing accent dot ↔ mirrored gradient line), tinted with the biome accent. Reads as a "place" header instead of plain text.

**Carousel dots**: gap tightened 4 → 5px (matches 18-stage row breathing room) + z-index bumped to 3 so vignette doesn't dim them.

**BATTLE button pulse**: new `@keyframes battlePulse` in `index.html` throbs the ember-orange box-shadow on a 2s ease-in-out cycle (12px → 22px blur, 0.45 → 0.80 opacity). Applied only when stage is unlocked; lock branch strips animation.

