## Concern D — Asset slot hooks (Architect 2026-05-02)

Architect locked visual direction: **ukiyo-e meets dark illustration** for menus
(painterly, paper-textured, ink-line, washed color). Combat keeps current
sprites. Procedural canvas from A-C is the immediate shipping path; illustration
commissions / AI-generated + cleaned art swap in via these hooks zero-rewrite.

**Three constants at the top of the menu paint block (`js/wg-game.js` ~line 351):**

```js
const BIOME_ART = {
  forest_summer: null, forest_autumn: null,
  cold_stone:    null, temple:        null,
  cave:          null, eldritch:      null,
};
const CHARACTER_PORTRAITS = {};
const RIFT_BIOMES = new Set();
```

Setting any value to a URL replaces the procedural path with an `<img>` overlay
(`decoding="async"`, `loading="lazy"`); the procedural canvas remains as the
in-DOM fallback. On `load` → procedural canvas hidden. On `error` → img is
removed from the DOM and the procedural path stays visible.

**Cross-IP rift intrusion** — when `stage.biome` is in `RIFT_BIOMES`, the
biome image **and** character portrait carry the `wg-rift-intrude` class:

```css
.wg-rift-intrude {
  filter: drop-shadow(0 0 8px rgba(192,96,255,0.6)) hue-rotate(15deg);
  animation: wgRiftGlitch 3.5s steps(1, end) infinite;
}
@keyframes wgRiftGlitch { /* 80ms pixel offset every ~3.5s */ }
```

Marks "this character / place doesn't fully belong" — violet drop-shadow + a
brief 80ms transform shake every ~3.5s. The keyframe owns `transform`, so
Concern D restructured the character portrait from `transform: translateX(-50%)`
centering to `left: calc(50% - 48px)` so the glitch shake doesn't undo the
centering on rift biomes.

**Header comment in `wg-game.js`** documents the slot:

```
// ART SLOTS: Set BIOME_ART[id] / CHARACTER_PORTRAITS[id] to a URL when
// illustrated assets ship. Cross-IP intrusions trigger violet drop-shadow +
// glitch keyframe.
```

**Files touched (Concern D):**
- `js/wg-game.js` — three slot consts + biome img branch + portrait img branch + portrait centering restructure (`translateX(-50%)` → `left: calc(50% - 48px)`)
- `index.html` — `.wg-rift-intrude` rule + `@keyframes wgRiftGlitch`

**Verification (Concern D):**
- `node --check build-v2/js/wg-game.js` → OK
- Live preview after reload, all slots null:
  - 2 canvases, 0 imgs (procedural path active)
  - Carousel scroll across stages 1→6 (Lantern Vigil → Pale Crossing → Hollow Shrine → Frostbound Watch → Glacier Mouth → Throat of Ice) — biomes render distinctly, no img elements appear
  - `getComputedStyle('.wg-rift-intrude')` resolves: `filter: drop-shadow(... rgba(192,96,255,0.6) 0 0 8px) hue-rotate(15deg)`, `animation-name: wgRiftGlitch`, `animation-duration: 3.5s`
  - Locked Stage 6 still renders biome + lock overlay + suppressed BATTLE pulse
  - Zero console errors
